	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's pretty normal for art direction for any project to create palettes to use as a style guide.<br /><br />As for why you'd want to use an NES-like palette but not an actual NES-palette, I don't see how that would have any use for meeting technical requirements, but it's fine as a stylistic choice, I suppose? Why would it matter to anyone but you?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


